{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Tutorial: Adding a Tip or Donation to the Cart page","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>This is a quick tutorial to show you how to add a field for donations on your cart page. It works by adding a product worth $0.01 multiple times via AJAX. </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://schroeder-kozey-and-wilderman397.myshopify.com/cart\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 75.97471022128556%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image \" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"donation box\" title src=\"/static/e3e92f8d5c9978be2a9495b28180de9c/dbb61/donation-box.png\" srcset=\"/static/e3e92f8d5c9978be2a9495b28180de9c/19bd1/donation-box.png 163w,\n/static/e3e92f8d5c9978be2a9495b28180de9c/d3bcb/donation-box.png 325w,\n/static/e3e92f8d5c9978be2a9495b28180de9c/dbb61/donation-box.png 650w,\n/static/e3e92f8d5c9978be2a9495b28180de9c/b938d/donation-box.png 949w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<p>You can see a demo of this <a href=\"http://schroeder-kozey-and-wilderman397.myshopify.com/cart\">here</a> (you&#x2019;ll have to add a product in the cart first). </p>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s get started! </p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Create a product for your donation</h2>\n<p>The first thing you need to do is create a product that will be your donation. This product will be a single-option, with a single variant worth $0.01. </p>\n<p><a href=\"/static/58b8a4771c546c7e89165687601c95c4/16abd/donation-product.png\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 80.21276595744682%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image alignnone size-full wp-image-2591\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"donation product\" title src=\"/static/58b8a4771c546c7e89165687601c95c4/dbb61/donation-product.png\" srcset=\"/static/58b8a4771c546c7e89165687601c95c4/19bd1/donation-product.png 163w,\n/static/58b8a4771c546c7e89165687601c95c4/d3bcb/donation-product.png 325w,\n/static/58b8a4771c546c7e89165687601c95c4/dbb61/donation-product.png 650w,\n/static/58b8a4771c546c7e89165687601c95c4/16abd/donation-product.png 940w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></a></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Add the donation product to a link list. </h2>\n<p>Create a link list called &#x201C;Donation&#x201D;. Add a product link, select &#x201C;Product&#x201D; under Links To, and then select the &#x201C;Donation&#x201D; product. It should look like this: </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/donation-linklist.png\"><img src=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/donation-linklist.png\" alt=\"donation linklist\" width=\"940\" height=\"323\" style=\"border:1px solid #ccc;\"></a></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Add a donation field to your cart page</h2>\n<p>This step is pretty theme-dependent. If you need a hand with placing and styling the textbox, please check with the designer of your theme or ask in the <a href=\"http://ecommerce.shopify.com/c/ecommerce-design\">design forums</a>.</p>\n<p>Grab the following code and place it inside your &#x201C;cart.liquid&#x201D; template. You may want to place is somewhere near your check out button. </p>\n<pre><code>\n<h3 class=\"cart-donation\">\n   <p>Donation or Tip: </p>\n   <input type=\"text\" id=\"donate\">\n</h3>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Add the donation script to theme.liquid</h2>\n<p>Inside your Template Editor, create a new snippet called &#x201C;donation-snippet&#x201D;. Add the contents of <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/Tetsuro/4403192/raw/85e4b6d9d22539c745d5f0e6c745e8226f2bc26f/gistfile1.txt\">this gist</a> inside it. </p>\n<p>Place the following code right before the &lt;/body&gt; tag in theme.liquid.</p>\n<pre><code>\n{% include &apos;donation-snippet&apos; %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<h2 class=\"step\">(Optional) Hide the donation product&#x2019;s price from the Checkout</h2>\n<p>You&#x2019;ll notice that on the checkout page, it&#x2019;ll show the quantity times $0.01 (shown below).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/checkout-price.png\"><img src=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/checkout-price.png\" alt=\"checkout price\" width=\"797\" height=\"557\" style=\"border:1px solid #ccc;\"></a></p>\n<p>If you&#x2019;re looking to hide this, you can add a bit off CSS in your &#x201C;checkout.css.liquid&#x201D; file to hide the price. </p>\n<pre><code>\nh3[title=&quot;Donation&quot;] + span{\n    display:none;\n}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Make sure the value of &#x201C;title&#x201D; is the title of your product, which should be &#x201C;Donation&#x201D; if you&#x2019;ve been following this tutorial :D.</p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">The End</h2>\n<p>That&#x2019;s all! Hope it helps.</p>\n</body></html>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-tutorial-adding-a-tip-or-donation-to-the-cart-page"}}